<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/601: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Vargas</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-14">May 14, 1938</date>.<lb/>[Received 8:14
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I take satisfaction in thanking you for the terms of your message,
                            Eminent Friend, who well interprets the spirit of solidarity of American
                            nations at the moment when the advocates of foreign doctrines attempted
                            a coup against Brazilian democracy. I reciprocate, and renew to Your
                            Excellency the assurance of my highest esteem.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Getulio Vargas</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>